Install Cordova:
=================
npm install -g cordova

Create Project:
===============
cordova create dmles-mobile mil.jmlfdc.dmles.mobile DmlesMobile

Add Platforms:
==============
All subsequent commands need to be run within the project's directory, or any subdirectories:

$ cd dmles-mobile
Add the platforms that you want to target your app. We will add the 'ios' and 'android' platform and ensure they get saved to config.xml:

$ cordova platform add ios --save
$ cordova platform add android --save

To check your current set of platforms:
=======================================
$ cordova platform ls

Build the App
==============
$ cordova build          // build all
$ cordova build ios      // build for ios only
$ cordova build andoid   // build for android only

Test the App
============	
$ cordova emulate android  // use emulator
$ cordova emulate ios  // use emulator

$ cordova run android  // test app directly
$ cordova run ios --device

Plugman
========
Is a tool used to install plugins outside of the Cordova or PhoneGap CLI 
$ npm install -g plugman

Plugins:
========
$ cordova plugin add cordova-plugin-console

